\[
\begin{aligned}
\mathbf{A}&=\bigl(-\sin\varphi\,\cos\gamma_p,\;\; \cos\varphi\,\cos\gamma_p,\;\; \cos\varphi\,\tan\alpha\,\cos\gamma_p\bigr) \\[4pt]
\mathbf{B}&=-F_k\bigl(0,\;\tan\alpha+\tan\gamma_p,\;\tan\alpha\,\tan\gamma_p-1\bigr)
\end{aligned}
\]

The cross product \(\mathbf{C}=\mathbf{A}\times\mathbf{B}=(x,y,z)\) simplifies to  

\[
\boxed{
\begin{aligned}
x &= F_k\,\cos\varphi\,\cos\gamma_p\;\bigl(1+\tan^{2}\alpha\bigr)
      \;=\;F_k\,\cos\varphi\,\cos\gamma_p\,\sec^{2}\alpha ,\\[4pt]
y &= F_k\,\sin\varphi\,\cos\gamma_p\;\bigl(1-\tan\alpha\,\tan\gamma_p\bigr),\\[4pt]
z &= F_k\,\sin\varphi\,\cos\gamma_p\;\bigl(\tan\alpha+\tan\gamma_p\bigr).
\end{aligned}
}
\]
